  <body>
    <h1>Corn and Beans</h1>
    <img src="../images/corn-and-beans.jpg" alt="Corn and Beans">

    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>This is an easy dish that can be prepared as a warm snack or a part of a bigger meal. It's healthy and won't raise your blood sugar. You can use whatever beans you have cooked on hand. As for the spices, used whatever complements your choice of bean. For black beans, you can try cumin and chili peppers. For black eyed peas, try thyme and cayenne.</p>

    <h2>Ingredients</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>85g frozen sweet corn</li>
      <li>60g cooked beans</li>
      <li>4g vinegar cayenne hot sauce</li>
      <li>3g salt</li>
      <li>2g spices</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Steps</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Cook your beans if you have not already done so</li>
      <li>Microwave the corn, beans, and 1g salt until they are hot</li>
      <li>Add the remaining ingredients.</li>
      <li>Stir</li>
      <li>Transfer to dish</li>
    </ol>
    
</html>
